sentences: Choi Whee-sung (Korean: 최휘성; born February 5, 1982), known professionally as Wheesung or by the stage name Realslow, is a South Korean R&B singer, record producer, and musical theatre actor.
Wheesung was born on February 5, 1982.
He began singing in his senior year.
He initially attended the Sun Moon University, under the journalism major but dropped out.

Wheesung left YG Entertainment after his contract expired in March 2006.
In late 2008, Wheesung has collaborated once again with Lee Hyori who featured as his girlfriend in his music video of "별이 지다.."
In 2009, Wheesung seeks help from producer Lee Hyun-do, they will collaborate to produce the new album which the release date has been set in August 2009.

2009–2011: POP/UP Entertainment =
In April 2009, Wheesung is the MC/host of a new Mnet TV show called "Pre Star-1 Show.
Every month about nine or ten teams will be introduced on Mnet.com and the team which receives most response from the netizens will be chosen onto the show.
Wheesung's Pre-Show 1 Show’ started airing on April 24 on Mnet Cable Channel.
On June 19, 2009, Wheesung and Lena Park held a concert in Los Angeles Disney Concert Hall.
After the concert, Wheesung planned to stay in Los Angeles for a month to work on his new album with producer Lee Hyun-do.
The new album is set to be released in August 2009.
On June 27 and July 4, Wheesung performed at "Insomnia Concert" and club Le Cercle in LA.
On July 11, he performed at the HALO nightclub in Hollywood.

In June 2009, Wheesung changed his label again from Orange Shock to POP/UP Entertainment, which houses stars like JK Kim Dong Wook and group M to M. Wheesung has decided to change his label because former producer, Park Gun Tae, concentrated more on producing and working by himself.
